[1] Case update
- Tue 18 Sep 2018. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., edited]
https://us13.campaign-archive.com/?u=89e5755d2cca4840b1af93176&id=6e1e9db638

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease dated 17 Sep 2018:
- A total of 142 cases of haemorrhagic fever were reported in the region, 111 confirmed and 31 probable.
- Of the 111 confirmed, 66 died and 38 are cured.
- 6 suspected cases are under investigation.
- No new confirmed cases notified.
- No new deaths

News of the response
Surveillance
------------
- The Angumu and Getthy [Geti] alerts in Ituri province were negative.

Support
-------
- On Tue 18 Sep 2018, Dr Oly Ilunga Kalenga, Minister of Health, traveled to Makeke, Mandima health zone, Ituri province to inaugurate the new Ebola treatment center (ETC) built by International Medical Corps (IMC). This 4th ETC of 50 beds will allow to quickly treat any suspected or confirmed case notified in this health zone close to that of Mangina [North Kivu], the epicenter of the current epidemic. The decision to build the ETC in Makeke was made last August [2018] when the coordination found that the 50-bed ETC in Mangina was filling up rapidly and could no longer accommodate additional patients given the rapid increase in confirmed and suspected cases. Since then, the epidemiological curve has been reversed at the epicenter and only sporadic and imported cases are still notified to Mangina and Makeke.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Mary Marshall

[Note there are no new cases reported and the suspect cases in Ituri province were demonstrated to be negative in laboratory testing. The case number holds in the following MoH report also, promising news that the outbreak is winding down. However, it is important to keep in mind that a single case that goes undetected can lead to reinitiation of a larger outbreak.

The other piece of good news is that the 4th Ebola treatment center in Makeke in Mandima health zone is completed. This center contains 50 beds and will facilitate testing and treatment of patients. - Mod.LK]

- Wed 19 Sep 2018. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., edited]
https://us13.campaign-archive.com/?u=89e5755d2cca4840b1af93176&id=ec37a38d3c

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease dated 18 Sep 2018:
- A total of 142 cases of haemorrhagic fever were reported in the region, 111 confirmed and 31 probable.
- Of the 111 confirmed, 66 died and 38 are cured.
- 9 suspected cases are under investigation.
- No new confirmed cases notified.
- No new deaths.

News of the response
Coordination of the response to Butembo
---------------------------------------
- On Wed 19 Sep 2018, Dr Oly Ilunga Kalenga, Minister of Health, and Dr Yokouide Allarangar, WHO Representative in DRC, traveled to Butembo with a joint delegation from the Ministry of Health, WHO, and UNICEF to see the evolution of the response in this important commercial city of North Kivu. They visited the new Ebola treatment center (ETC) built by Médecins Sans Frontières [MSF] in Butembo which will be able to welcome its 1st patients in the coming days. They also spoke at length with the city's religious authorities, including the Bishop of the Diocese of Butembo-Beni, Msgr. Melchisédech Sikuli Paluku, and the representatives of the Church of Christ in Congo, the revival churches and the independent churches. Then they met the members of the Federation of Enterprises of Congo (FEC) with whom they spoke about the preventive measures to be taken by these large traders.

Vaccination
-----------
- Since the beginning of vaccination on 8 Aug 2018, 10 352 people have been vaccinated, including 3935 in Mabalako [North Kivu], 3350 in Beni [North Kivu], 1542 in Mandima [Ituri], 754 in Butembo [North Kivu], 314 in Katwa [North Kivu], 220 in Masereka [North Kivu], 121 in Oicha [North Kivu], 51 in Komanda [Ituri], and 65 in Kinshasa (medical staff to deploy).

--
Communicated by:
Greg Folkers
NIAID, NIH
<gfolkers@nih.gov>
and
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Mary Marshall

[Case numbers hold at 142, and a remarkable 10 352 people have been vaccinated! Great work by all those involved in the effort. - Mod.LK]

