[3] Negative tests in Mukambo and Geti
19 Sep 2018. No Ebola virus in Mukambo and Geti after laboratory analysis
[Media Congo; in French, machine trans, edited]
https://www.mediacongo.net/article-actualite-42446_ituri_pas_de_virus_ebola_a_mukambo_et_a_geti_apres_analyse_au_laboratoire.html

Samples taken from a woman who died last weekend [15-16 Sep 2018] in Mukambo in Mahagi territory [North Kivu] and a suspect case in Geti in Irumu territory [Ituri] and sent to the mobile laboratory in Beni, North Kivu for analysis, were negative.

The vice governor of Ituri province who delivers the news to Bunia News however invites the population not to give up and continue to observe the hygiene measures.

"Both suspected cases were negative after analysis at the laboratory of the National Institute for Biological Research, INRB. But it does not mean that we should cross our arms, we ask the people to keep the rules of hygiene and as soon as there is a suspect case, to go to the nearest medical facility," said Pacifique Keta Upar.

Ituri province in northeastern DRC is under threat from this deadly virus and part of its territory, Mambasa, neighboring Beni in North Kivu, epicenter of the disease, is already affected.

The movement of population between the 2 neighboring provinces is significant and the risk of contagion remains high despite some preventive measures taken by the authorities, including washing hands at the various entry points.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Mary Marshall

[These negative cases are also reported in the DRC Ministry of Health epidemiological situation report of 17 Sep 2018, above. - Mod.LK

